  "text": "A little late to post this 😊. I was part of the EuroPython Beginners' Day Unconference held at Prague. I joined the panel discussion on “From Junior to Senior.”\nThanks to Daria Linhart Grudzien and Honza Javorek for the invitation and for organizing a wonderful event.\nIt was great to share the stage with Gábor Ambrózy who is Tech leader and a pro in public speaking / panel discussions. Thanks again to Daria Linhart Grudzien for moderating and steering the discussion.\nWe spoke about real world scenarios of climbing the ladder from Junior to Senior and shared honest thoughts. The audience was amazing. Many of them were self-taught and about to start their programming journey.\nI believe more such events like this should happen. They inspire and guide beginners, juniors 🚀. I wish I had such events when I was a beginner !\n\n#europython #europython2025 #beginner #developer #programmer",
